## How to Use

The application has 4 tabs:

### 1. ⚙️ Configure
- Fill in **Source Database** connection details (type, host, port, database name, username, password)
- Click **Test Connection** — on success, available tables are listed
- Select the **source table** and **timestamp column**
- Fill in **Target Database** details and click **Test Connection**
- Enter the **target table name** (it will be created automatically if it doesn't exist)
- Click **Next: Configure Mapping**

### 2. 🗂 Mapping
- Select a **time bucket size** (1 min to 1 day)
- Set the **date/time range** of source data to process
- For each numeric column, choose an **aggregation function** (MIN, MAX, MEAN, etc.)
- Click **Save Mapping** to store the configuration for reuse
- Click **Load Saved** to restore a previously saved mapping
- Click **Next: Run Job**

### 3. ▶ Run Job
- Review the **job summary** (source, target, bucket, range, mappings)
- Click **▶ Run Aggregation Job**
- Watch the **real-time progress bar** and status badge
- View **5 KPI cards** and **2 live charts** (Ingestion Volume + Processing Latency)
- Any errors are shown as readable messages (not raw stack traces)

### 4. 📋 History
- View all previous job runs with start time, end time, source/target table, row count, and status
- Click **Export CSV** to download the full job history
- Click **Refresh** to reload the latest entries

