## Architecture Overview

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│               Browser (index.html)           │
│                                             │
│  Configure → Mapping → Run Job → History    │
│                                             │
│  Fetch API calls  ←──────────────────────┐  │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┼──┘
                                           │ HTTP REST API
┌──────────────────────────────────────────▼──┐
│           Flask Backend (Python)             │
│                                             │
│  /api/test-connection  → DBClientMock        │
│  /api/discover-schema  → Column inspector    │
│  /api/jobs  (POST)     → Job runner          │
│  /api/jobs/<id>        → Status polling      │
│  /api/jobs/history     → SQLite ledger       │
│  /api/config-mapping   → JSON file store     │
│  /api/kpis             → Aggregated metrics  │
│  /api/chart-data       → Chart feed          │
│                                             │
│  Background Thread (asyncio loop)            │
│  └─ run_async_aggregation_worker()           │
│     ├─ Extract data from source DB           │
│     ├─ Apply aggregation (pandas resample)   │
│     └─ Write results to target DB            │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────┘
           │                        │
    ┌──────▼──────┐         ┌───────▼───────┐
    │  Source DB   │         │   Target DB    │
    │ (SQLite demo │         │ (SQLite demo   │
    │  / real DB)  │         │  / real DB)    │
    └─────────────┘         └───────────────┘
           │
    ┌──────▼──────────────────┐
    │  pulseops_engine_        │
    │  metadata.db (SQLite)    │
    │  — Job history store     │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

**Data Flow:**
1. User fills in source/target DB config in the browser
2. Browser POSTs credentials to Flask backend (never stored in browser)
3. Backend tests connection and returns available tables
4. User selects table → backend discovers numeric columns
5. User configures mappings and clicks Run
6. Backend spawns an async background worker
7. Worker extracts raw data → applies pandas resample aggregations → writes to target
8. Frontend polls `/api/jobs/<id>` every 800ms for progress updates
9. On completion, job is logged to SQLite history

